revision.text:
{{Infobox video game |title= .detuned |image = Detuned.png |caption = |developer = [[.theprodukkt]] |publisher = [[Sony Computer Entertainment Europe]] |designer = [[Christoph Mütze|Christoph "giZMo" Mütze]] |composer = Leonard "paniq" Ritter |series = |engine = [[Altona (engine)|Altona]] |released = {{vgrelease|JP|September 17, 2009|EU|October 15, 2009|NA|October 15, 2009}} |genre = [[Interactive art]] |modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] |platforms= [[PlayStation 3]] }} '''''.detuned''''' is a [[demoscene]] project by the German demogroup [[.theprodukkt]] (also known as [[Farbrausch]]), released on the [[PlayStation 3]]. It was initially released on September 20, 2009 in Japan, and on October 15 in Europe and North America. It is the second [[demo (computer programming)|demo]] released on the PlayStation 3 after ''[[Linger in Shadows]]''.
''.detuned'' features a man sitting in a chair surrounded by a psychedelic environment. The player can switch into various modes, and using the trigger buttons and right analogue stick, apply certain effects on the man, which e.g. make his head shrink or apply a post-processing filter on the visuals and music. The player is also able to load their own music in.
==Reception== {{Video game reviews |GR=40.33% <ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.gamerankings.com/ps3/960626-detuned/|title=.detuned|website=GameRankings|accessdate=October 27, 2014}}</ref> |MC=46/100 <ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/detuned|title=.detuned|website=Metacritic|accessdate=October 27, 2014}}</ref> |EuroG={{Rating|6|10}} <ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.eurogamer.it/articles/detuned-recensione|title=.detuned|last=Mottura|first=Marco|website=EuroGamer|date=October 29, 2009|accessdate=October 27, 2014}} {{it icon}}</ref> |IGN={{Rating|4|10}}<ref name="ign">{{citeweb|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2009/10/16/detuned-review|title=.detuned Review|last=Roper|first=Chris|website=IGN|date=October 16, 2009|accessdate=October 27, 2014}}</ref> }}
[[IGN]] cited the lack of lasting appeal as the biggest problem about ''.detuned'', saying that "selling for $2.99 in the US PlayStation Store, that's about a dollar per minute of entertainment". Overall they awarded the game a 4/10, with a 1/10 on Lasting Appeal.<ref name="ign"/>
